# Vivint Smart Home
**Category:** ventures  
**Domain:** smart home technology / home security  
**Website:** vivint.com

## Overview
Vivint Smart Home is a leading provider of smart home security and automation systems, offering integrated devices such as doorbell cameras, smart locks, thermostats, and motion sensors. The company was founded in 1999 (as APX Alarm Security Solutions) by Todd Pedersen in Provo, Utah, and rebranded to Vivint in 2011. Vivint’s platform combines hardware with a cloud-based app and professional monitoring services, giving homeowners remote control and real-time alerts.

The company grew rapidly through a direct-to-consumer sales model and by acquiring related technology firms. Its proprietary smart hub (the Vivint Smart Hub) and AI-powered cameras have set it apart in the residential security market. Vivint was acquired by NRG Energy in 2012, taken private by Blackstone Group in 2017, and later merged with Mosaic in 2020 to form Vivint Smart Home, Inc. It remains one of the largest home automation companies in North America, serving over 2 million customers.

## Utah connection
Vivint is headquartered in Provo, Utah, and has long been a major employer in the state’s technology sector. The company’s roots in Utah Valley helped spur growth in the local tech ecosystem, attracting talent and supporting ancillary services. Vivint’s presence also contributed to Utah’s reputation as a hub for innovation in smart home and security technologies.

